026 security incident","url":"https://vercel.com/kb/bulletin/vercel-april-2026-security-incident","score":31,"flags":1,"comment_count":3,"description":"\u003cp\u003esome context: \u003ca href=\"https://nitter.net/DiffeKey/status/2045813085408051670\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://nitter.net/DiffeKey/status/2045813085408051670\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"some context: https://nitter.net/DiffeKey/status/2045813085408051670","submitter_user":"figsoda","user_is_author":false,"tags":["security","web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/aaqbdy","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/aaqbdy/vercel_april_2026_security_incident"},{"short_id":"30vbek","created_at":"2026-04-20T04:09:21.000-05:00","title":"bpfvet: analyzes compiled .bpf.o files and reports minimum kernel version, helpers, maps, and portability issues","url":"https://github.com/boratanrikulu/bpfvet","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eBuilt this to answer \"what's the oldest kernel this BPF program can run on?\" without reading changelogs.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFeed it any .bpf.o file and it tells you:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMinimum kernel version (computed from helpers, prog types, map types)b\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTransport mechanism (RingBuf, PerfEventArray, maps)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCO-RE coverage and BTF presence\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSuperseded helper usage (bpf_probe_read -\u0026gt; bpf_probe_read_kernel)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWorks on compiled ELF, not source-language agnostic.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Built this to answer \"what's the oldest kernel this BPF program can run on?\" without reading changelogs.\r\n\r\nFeed it any .bpf.o file and it tells you:  \r\n- Minimum kernel version (computed from helpers, prog types, map types)b \r\n- Transport mechanism (RingBuf, PerfEventArray, maps)  \r\n- CO-RE coverage and BTF presence   \r\n- Superseded helper usage (bpf_probe_read -\u003e bpf_probe_read_kernel)\r\n\r\nWorks on compiled ELF, not source-language agnostic.","submitter_user":"boratanrikulu","user_is_author":true,"tags":["linux","networking"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/30vbek","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/30vbek/bpfvet_analyzes_compiled_bpf_o_files"},{"short_id":"qxhzxh","created_at":"2026-04-19T14:39:51.000-05:00","title":"corpus: self-hosted listenbrainz and last.fm frontend","url":"https://github.com/mtmn/corpus","score":10,"flags":1,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eWorks as a self-hosted proxy that fetches listening history from either Last.fm or MusicBrainz, adds metadata from MusicBrainz (falling back to Last.fm and Discogs) and caches cover images to an S3 bucket. Everything is stored in DuckDB (each user has their own database) and it's been humming along quite well even for larger profiles (200k scrobbles).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI always worry that these services can disappear without a warning and with them also amazingly extensive listening histories.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI used LLMs quite a lot as I was learning about Purescript and Elm on the fly on the weekends and this is one of the projects I have been thinking about for a long time since other alternatives just seemed a bit lackluster.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Works as a self-hosted proxy that fetches listening history from either Last.fm or MusicBrainz, adds metadata from MusicBrainz (falling back to Last.fm and Discogs) and caches cover images to an S3 bucket. Everything is stored in DuckDB (each user has their own database) and it's been humming along quite well even for larger profiles (200k scrobbles).\r\n\r\nI always worry that these services can disappear without a warning and with them also amazingly extensive listening histories.\r\n\r\nI used LLMs quite a lot as I was learning about Purescript and Elm on the fly on the weekends and this is one of the projects I have been thinking about for a long time since other alternatives just seemed a bit lackluster.","submitter_user":"miro","user_is_author":true,"tags":["elm","haskell","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/qxhzxh","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/qxhzxh/corpus_self_hosted_listenbrainz_last_fm"},{"short_id":"b5klfi","created_at":"2026-04-20T06:50:49.000-05:00","title":"How LLVM optimizes power sums (2019)","url":"https://kristerw.blogspot.com/2019/04/how-llvm-optimizes-geometric-sums.html","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"daniel_alp","user_is_author":false,"tags":["c","c++","compilers"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/b5klfi","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/b5klfi/how_llvm_optimizes_power_sums_2019"},{"short_id":"tttexr","created_at":"2026-04-18T09:35:30.000-05:00","title":"SQLite prefixes its temp files with `etilqs_`","url":"https://avi.im/blag/2026/etilqs/","score":90,"flags":2,"comment_count":17,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"av","user_is_author":true,"tags":["databases"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/tttexr","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/tttexr/sqlite_prefixes_its_temp_files_with"},{"short_id":"9ohf8f","created_at":"2026-04-19T09:36:53.000-05:00","title":"postmarketOS Conference","url":"https://postmarketos.org/conference/","score":25,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"hugoarnal","user_is_author":false,"tags":["event","linux","mobile"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/9ohf8f","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/9ohf8f/postmarketos_conference"},{"short_id":"dantuo","created_at":"2026-04-20T05:24:36.000-05:00","title":"Casilda 1.2.4 Released","url":"https://blogs.gnome.org/xjuan/2026/04/19/casilda-1-2-4-released/","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"FedericoSchonborn","user_is_author":false,"tags":["c","graphics"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dantuo","comm